The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Tokyo/New Delhi, Dec. 17: Japans Sumitomo Chemical Company will acquire Mumbai-based agro-chemical manufacturer New Chemi Industries for an undisclosed amount. The acquisition will complement the existing product lines offered by Sumitomo Chemical in the country through its subsidiary, SC Enviro Agro India Pvt Ltd, as New Chemi has a large portfolio of crop protection products.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 17: State-run NTPC is ready to buy gas for its Kawas and Gandhar projects at a price decided by an empowered group of ministers (EGoM) as the projects will suffer without the fuel. We have approached the government to allocate gas, and at whatever price the EGoM decides, NTPC chairman Arup Roy Choudhury said.                            
	 Pune, Dec. 17: The Centre will issue its directive on export of five lakh tonnes of excess sugar production this week, agriculture minister Sharad Pawar said today. The government took the decision permitting export of five lakh tonnes of sugar yesterday and a notification to that effect will be issued this week, he said.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 17: Interim regulator PFRDA has decided to enhance incentives to distributors from Rs 50 to Rs 150 for each subscriber for the current financial year, a move aimed at popularising the citizen pension plan, which has received lukewarm response.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 17: ONGC Videsh, the overseas arm of Oil and Natural Gas Corp, is hoping to sign an agreement to take a stake in the Trebs and Titov in the Arctic during Russian President Dmitry Medvedevs visit next week.                            
	 New York, Dec. 17: Makers of BlackBerry, Research In Motion (RIM), have posted a 45 per cent jump in net income at $911 million for the third quarter ended November 27, driven by record sales of smartphones.                            
	 Mumbai, Dec. 17: The Bombay Stock Exchange, the National Stock Exchange, forex and money markets were closed today to observe Muharram.
                                                                                                                          
